name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
【Multiple pictures】
Recently, Liu Xiaobo, a well-known financial commentator, compiled the data of the "System Strength Index" for some cities and provinces in 2023 based on the annual reports of provident funds in various places. The series of pictures are currently blocked on Weibo. According to his description, the "System Strength Index" was first proposed by him three years ago. It is very valuable for examining the economic and social activity of a city or region, and whether it is worth investing.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Guangdong Province
The "system strength index" of 21 cities in Guangdong is very fragmented and polarized. Dongguan, Shenzhen, and Foshan, cities with a large number of migrant populations and a high degree of marketization, have "system strength indexes" below 20%.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Jiangsu Province
Xuzhou has the highest “institutional intensity index” in Jiangsu, which is significantly higher than other Jiangsu cities and has obvious northern characteristics.
The indexes of Suzhou and Changzhou are even lower than those of Dongguan and Shenzhen. In the northern part of Jiangsu, the "institutional strength index" is overall high, and in the southern Suzhou, Wuxi and Changzhou areas it is the lowest.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Zhejiang Province
Hangzhou has the lowest "system strength index" in Zhejiang, at only 14.3%. It should be noted that the provident funds of provincial agencies in each province are managed separately and are not calculated in the provincial capital. Therefore, the data of provincial capitals do not include provincial agencies.
Lishui, Zhoushan, and Quzhou have the highest system strength index in Zhejiang, which is also expected.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Shandong Province
Weihai's "system strength index" is the lowest in Shandong, which is beyond my expectation, but the data has been verified and it is correct. The second is Qingdao. These two cities in Shandong are the only ones below 30%, and they are the most market-oriented.
Zaozhuang, Heze, Jining, and Yantai all exceed 66%, and the characteristics of northern cities are obvious.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Liaoning Province
Dalian's system intensity index is only 22.92%, the lowest in Liaoning; followed by Shenyang, reaching 42%.
The intra-system intensity index of most cities in Liaoning exceeds 70%, showing the strength of the "in-system" in Northeast China. This is also an important reason why the Northeast cannot retain people and young people have gone out to make a living.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Gansu Province
We often use the term "Northeastization" to describe a place's economy losing its vitality, but the situation in the northwest is more typical. All prefecture-level cities in Gansu have an institutional strength index of more than 70%, and four prefecture-level cities have exceeded 90%.
What does exceeding 90% mean? Basically, "there is no world outside the system."

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Henan Province
Henan’s system strength index is also generally high, but Jiyuan, a county-level city directly under the province, has the lowest index, followed by Luohe and Zhengzhou.
The system strength index of most cities in Henan exceeds 60%, so the proportion of Henan people who go out to make a living is also relatively high.
